    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-02-14T02:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-02-14T02:30:00-05:00" n="211"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d211">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">788.5 <gloss target="#t_MAP1">MAP</gloss>/2–1450:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wiley</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-02-14T11:00:00+03:30"
                            >February 14, 1950—11 a. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>259. <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 222, February 8.<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d211fn1">Not printed.</note> Department inform Army, Navy, Air. In
                    talk with Shah February 12 he spoke most emphatically of need of US to decide
                    role expected of Iran in event of war and of necessity that he be informed of
                    place of Iran in US strategic planning. Shah stated he could handle internal
                    security with relatively small force but that it was very costly and under
                    present circumstances useless maintain present size army. Therefore, if US
                    expects Iran to oppose possible Soviet invasion he should be so informed without
                    delay.</p>
                <p>Shah expressed sense of considerable urgency re foregoing.</p>
                <p>This conversation with Shah strengthens my belief it would be most valuable were
                    senior US Army spokesman to visit Iran, <gloss target="#t_Embtel1"
                        >Embtel</gloss> 243, February 13.<note n="1" xml:id="d211fn2">Not
                        printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wiley</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
